<font color="#FF0000">THE FALL OF SAIGON AND ME</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan  7  2:34:31 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I was on the Rapid Deployment Force for rescue at the 304th ARRSq in Portland, Oregon.  We were in the process of being deployed as it fell, but it came so quickly that we couldn't get there.  Thus, I almost went there for a second time.  I remember being called for &quot;A two-week TDY to an undisclosed location,&quot; and being told that all the PJ's in the unit had volunteered to go.  I told my profs at Oregon State University that I might not be able to take finals, and remember their perplexed look when I couldn't tell them why.  It was an interesting time.<br><br>
We had a Vietnamese student who had been cut off from his government support somewhat earlier, and he was in tears.  It was a tough time for him.<br><br>

